    <section name="Overview">
      <p>
        This <a href="http://maven.apache.org/">Maven</a> plugin creates an
        archive with <a href="https://docs.jboss.org/author/display/MODULES/Home">JBoss modules</a>
        to be installed to a
        <a href="https://www.jboss.org/jbossas">JBoss 7</a> server installation.
      </p>
      <p>
        Crafting the modules by hand is more cumbersome than to define a recipe
        that allows to construct the modules folder with all dependencies
        already defined by a
        <a href="http://maven.apache.org/pom.html">Maven POM</a>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Please refer to
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="usage-modules.html">Usage Modules</a></li>
        <li><a href="jboss-modules-descriptor-doc.html">Modules XSD</a></li>
        <li><a href="import-modules.html">Import Module Descriptors</a></li>
        <li><a href="usage-jandex.html">Usage Jandex</a></li>
        <li><a href="usage-index.html">Usage Index</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        for details on how to use this plugin.
      </p>
      <p>
        In <a href="plugin-info.html">Goals</a> you'll find a short description
        of the goals and its parameters.
      </p>
      <p>
        Please note that this plugin only supports Maven from 3.1.x and up due to
        incompatibilities to the <a href="http://eclipse.org/aether/">Aether</a>
        implementation used by Maven. Please refer to
        <a href="http://www.smartics.eu/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=843">Bug 843</a>
        for details. If you are looking for support for Maven 3.0.x, please
        refer to <a href="${webroot}/${project.groupId}/${project.artifactId}/">versions 0.x</a>
        of this plugin.
      </p>
    </section>
